Acknowledgements
----------------

This project is built on top of years of community reverse-engineering work.
In particular it is informed by:

  - sq5bpf's UV-K5 reverse engineering and `k5prog` reference implementation
    (https://github.com/sq5bpf/uvk5-reverse-engineering, GPLv3)
  - The CHIRP driver `f4hwn.fusion.chirp.v5.4.0.py` by F4HWN, EGZUMER, JOC2,
    bundled with the F4HWN Fusion firmware (Apache 2.0 / GPL-2 dual)
  - The amnemonic Quansheng_UV-K5_Firmware project communication notes
  - The F4HWN Fusion firmware itself
    (https://github.com/armel/uv-k1-k5v3-firmware-custom)
  - The kk7ds CHIRP project (https://github.com/kk7ds/chirp), used as
    reference for the legacy UV-K5 V1/V2 stock memory map

The protocol implementation in `kradio/protocol.py` is a clean-room
re-implementation that follows the published specs and the structure of the
CHIRP driver, but contains no copied code from any of those projects.
